title: Beef Enchilada Dip
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet. Drain. Add in onion and garlic and cook until tender, about 3 minutes. Stir in enchilada sauce and top with grated cheese. Cover and allow cheese to melt, about 3 more minutes.
Top with sour cream and serve with tortilla chips.
ingredients: 2 cups grated Monterrey Jack or cheddar cheese
